"sleepsinging" gives birth to many of the ancient songs, whose melodies' ring can be noticed even in the music of today. "Sleepcrawling" occurs when a man's soul is too weakened due to stress. "Sleepflying" has no confirmed cases as of today. "Sleephowling" speaks of royal blood.

What people do not know is that even though sleepwalking is a relatively common condition, there also exist less known rare variation - "sleepwriting", in which a man begins to write mysterious tomes in arcane languages with his eyes shut, it is common for occultists;

Bodybuilders who experiment with higher doses of glycine sometimes experience an extremely rare phenomenon called "sleeptraining".

It consists of sleepwalking to the gym and, without waking up, beginning to lift. The puzzling part is that these workout look nothing like usual...

... routines, but consist of all manner of highly unusual or outright never seen before exercises, performed in seemingly random numbers of sets and reps.

Reported cases often become basis for new lifting methods and styles of training. This is how the Arnold press was born.
